1.title: Ganges River
1.description: A 2,525 km river in India and Bangladesh, sacred in Hinduism and vital for agriculture.

2.title: Yangtze River
2.description: Asia's longest river (6,300 km) flowing through China, home to the Three Gorges Dam.

3.title: Mekong River
3.description: Flows through six Asian countries, supporting fishing, rice farming, and biodiversity.

4.title: Nile River
4.description: World's longest river (6,650 km) running through 11 African countries into the Mediterranean.

5.title: Amazon River
5.description: South America's largest river by discharge, surrounded by vast rainforest ecosystems.

6.title: Mount Everest
6.description: Highest mountain on Earth (8,848 m) on the Nepal–China border, part of the Himalayas.

7.title: Sahara Desert
7.description: Largest hot desert in the world, spanning over 9 million km² in North Africa.

8.title: Great Wall of China
8.description: 21,000 km ancient fortification protecting China's northern borders.

9.title: Sydney Opera House
9.description: Iconic UNESCO World Heritage site in Australia, famous for its sail-shaped design.

10.title: Eiffel Tower
10.description: Paris landmark built in 1889, standing 324 m tall and visited by millions annually.

11.title: Victoria Falls
11.description: Waterfall on the Zambezi River at the border of Zambia and Zimbabwe, 'Smoke that Thunders'.

12.title: Mount Kilimanjaro
12.description: Africa's highest peak (5,895 m) in Tanzania, a dormant volcano with glacier caps.

13.title: Statue of Liberty
13.description: Gift from France to the USA in 1886, symbolizing freedom, located in New York Harbor.

14.title: Machu Picchu
14.description: 15th-century Inca citadel in Peru, set high in the Andes Mountains.

15.title: Antarctic Ice Sheet
15.description: Largest single mass of ice on Earth, covering about 98% of Antarctica.
